wikipedia_page.main: Rev. Dr Laurence F. Renehan (1797–1857) was an Irish Roman Catholic priest and President of St Patrick's College, Maynooth in County Kildare from 1845 to 1857. (St. Patrick's College is now formally the Pontifical University and National Seminary of Ireland, but is better known simply as Maynooth College. As such, it shares a campus and works in close cooperation with the National University of Ireland, Maynooth.)
